Lexical Co-occurrence 2.1 Evidence-based Models of Context Evidence-based models represent context as a set of features, say words, that are observed to co-occur with, and thereby predict, a word (Yarowsky, 1992; Golding and Schabes, 1996; Karow and Edelman, 1996; Ng and Lee, 1996).
